      tidbit: 'Stephen King threw the first draft of Carrie in the trash — his wife Tabitha retrieved it, read it, and told him he had something. Without that intervention, the book that launched his career might have been landfill.',
      expandedNarrative: 'Stephen King was born in Portland, Maine in 1947 and has set most of his fiction in the state\'s fictional geography — Castle Rock, Derry, Jerusalem\'s Lot are real places at heart, recognizable to anyone who knows small-town Maine. He wrote Carrie while teaching high school English, threw the draft in the trash because he thought it wasn\'t working, and his wife Tabitha retrieved and read it. She told him to keep going. Carrie sold to Doubleday for $2,500; the paperback rights sold for $400,000. He has published over sixty novels, sold more than 350 million books, and is the most widely read American fiction writer of the last half-century. He continues to live in Bangor, Maine.',
