      expandedNarrative: 'Edgar Allan Poe was born in Boston in 1809 and is most associated with Baltimore, where he lived during a crucial period of his career and where he died in mysterious circumstances in October 1849. He was found on the streets of Baltimore in a state of delirium, wearing clothes that were not his own, and died four days later without ever being able to explain his condition. The cause of death has never been determined. He is buried at Westminster Hall and Burying Ground, where every year on January 19th — his birthday — a mysterious figure in black leaves roses and a half-bottle of cognac on his grave. The tradition continued anonymously for decades. Poe\'s Baltimore house on North Amity Street is preserved as a museum.',
