      expandedNarrative: 'Louise Erdrich was born in Little Falls, Minnesota in 1954, of Ojibwe and German-American descent, and has written a cycle of interconnected novels set in North Dakota spanning a century of Native American and immigrant life — one of the great sustained fictional projects in American literature. She owns Birchbark Books in Minneapolis, a small independent bookstore specializing in Native American literature and art, where she is a frequent presence. She won the Pulitzer Prize for Fiction in 2021 for The Night Watchman, based on her grandfather\'s work opposing an act of Congress that would have dismantled tribal sovereignty. She was the first Native American author to win the Pulitzer Prize for Fiction.',
